text: Polyaxon v0.3.5 is out, notable changes: lazy collection of logs, archiving period for entities, tpu scheduling, better smoothing for line charts, better UI, multiple cmds, stable hptuning. The release also include several internal fixes and improvements: https:// docs.polyaxon.com/release_notes/ #035 …

Extremely happy to get @PolyaxonAI working smoothly after battling (=learning Kubernetes) a few days. Next on my ToDo list is @MLflowOrg . Fascinating to see which FOSS platform for ML Ops catches the most audience.

Here's a blogpost about the new changes in the 0.2.3 release. And we are sorry about the issue with the events that impacted the experiments' statuses https:// medium.com/polyaxon/polya xon-0-2-3-experiment-stability-better-tracking-better-visualization-b81f318efbd1 …
The saved searches now will include the custom columns (metrics/params)
We improved the metrics visualisation, you can compare metrics, create new widgets, and save different charts views.

We added better tracking and instrumentation for experiment. Now you can track experiments outside of a Polyaxon deployment, and report metrics, tags, environment run, ... to Polyaxon to compare results with other experiments.
We fixed one big issue with dropped events impacting the stability of experiment's statuses.

It's good to hear that you generally manage to pass the bus test", I did not know about this term until I started giving demos and helping teams customize @PolyaxonAI , and most often I hear that it's a cool project with very low bus factor. Very inspiring talk"

Sure, it can definitely be useful to work in an interpreter. Data munging or data exploration is a good example of that, as is exploring a new library. I think most research groups need better infrastructure and workflow. I hope @PolyaxonAI continues to catch on for that.

Polyaxon 0.1.8 is out, highlights from the release: * Support and integration of private registries * First draft to allow users to use S3, GCS, and Azure storage in addition to k8s persistent volumes * More dashboard meta-data: e.g. node used for scheduling ... * Bug fixes
Polyaxon does not provide model serving, the focus is currently around model training and experimentation.
Can polyaxon be used for serving predictions?

Polyaxon 0.1.7 is out: * New integrations with slack, hipchat, discord, mattermost, ... * Email integration * More control about jobs scheduling * Better usability and compliance with filtering, bookmarks, history and activity logs

Learn how you can mount multiple data and outputs volumes for you #DL and #ML experiments with Polyaxon https:// medium.com/polyaxon/mount ing-multiple-data-and-outputs-volumes-41f2d912f2f8 … pic.twitter.com/eexW7LmbbV

* Data and outputs: it's possible now to mount multiple data and outputs volumes, the specification has now a persistence subsection to give the users more control over what data to use and where to store outputs and artifacts.
* Updated UI to include more data about your experiments and jobs * Basic line charts for metrics * Tensorboards can be created for projects, experiments, and groups of experiments

* Replication for API, workers, and monitors * Possibility to allow workers to spike, this is important for hp tuning to consume more CPU to converge faster during each iteration. * Download internal commits made by Polyaxon * Download experiment and jobs outputs

* Filtering of experiments/jobs/groups, the docs have a query specification for more info on how to construct search filters, e.g. started_at:2015-01-01..2018-01-20, tags:foo|bar, metrics__loss:<=0.1" * Sorting by different attributes: -created_at, updated_at..."
* Generic job specification, for creating data processing and post-experiment processing * Tagging for projects, experiments, experiments groups, and jobs

* Add NFS provisioner * Add event management and backbone for creating notifications and integrations. This is the base for the next release with slack and other integrations.

* Add advanced nodes scheduling for experiments and jobs: Previously users could set a default node selectors for core and experiments. Now they have the ability to override these selectors per experiment, experiment job for distributed runs, notebook, and tensorboard.
